[1] Global as of 25 May 2022 (AFP WPV1 Pakistan, AFP cVDPV2 Chad, DR Congo, Niger, Yemen, ES Djibouti, Ghana, Nigeria, Somalia)
Date: Thu 26 May 2022
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative/WHO [edited]
https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update as of 25 May 2022, World Health Organization
---------------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 1
Environment: 1
Others: 0
New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 25
Environment: 7
Others: 3

Headlines:
• The need for speed: polio outbreak response (https://polioeradication.org/news-post/the-need-for-speed-polio-outbreak-response/). This article looks at recent closures of cVDPV outbreaks in the African region and highlights the importance of swift response in stopping transmission.

• Following its meeting in April 2022, the latest report from the Independent Monitoring Board (IMB) with the latest progress on polio eradication has been published and is available at https://polioeradication.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/21st-IMB-report-20220430.pdf.

• This week, the WHO World Health Assembly (WHA) is convening in Geneva. The GPEI has prepared 2 reports which will inform Member State discussions, namely on polio eradication, and on polio transition planning and post-certification. The reports are available at https://polioeradication.org/tools-and-library/policy-reports/reports-to-who-governing-bodies/.

• nOPV2 rollout: Approximately 350m doses of nOPV2 have been administered across 18 countries under its WHO Emergency Use Listing (EUL). An additional 18 countries have met the requirements for use in the event of an outbreak. Visit https://polioeradication.org/nopv2/ for more information on nOPV2.

Summary of new polioviruses this week:
- Afghanistan: 1 WPV1 positive environmental sample
- Pakistan: 1 WPV1 case
- Chad: 2 cVDPV2 cases
- Djibouti: 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- DR Congo: 10 cVDPV2 cases
- Ghana: 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- Niger: 1 cVDPV2 case and 1 positive environmental sample
- Nigeria: 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample
- Somalia: 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample
- Yemen: 12 cVDPV2 cases

Afghanistan
• No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. There was 1 WPV1 case reported in 2022 and 4 in 2021. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 43.
• 1 WPV1 positive environmental sample was reported in Nangarhar province.

Pakistan
• 1 WPV1 case was reported in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa bringing the number of 2022 cases to 3. There was 1 WPV1 case in 2021 while the total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 8.

Benin
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 3 cases reported in 2021.

Burkina Faso
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 2 cases reported in 2021.

Cameroon
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 3 cases reported in 2021.

Central African Republic
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were no cases reported in 2021.

Chad
• 2 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; 1 each in Batha and N'djamena. There are 3 cases reported in 2022.

Congo (Republic of)
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 2 cases reported in 2021.

Côte d'Ivoire
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were no cases reported in 2021.

Djibouti
• 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported in Djibouti and Arta provinces. There are 12 positive environmental samples reported in the country, all linked to the virus circulating in Yemen.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
• 10 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week; 8 in Maniema and 1 each in Nord-Kivu and Tanganyika. The number of 2022 cases now stands at 47. There were 28 cases in 2021.

Egypt
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported. There are 14 positive samples reported in the country.
• An internal surveillance review is scheduled for this month [May 2022], as part of preparations for the expected Outbreak Response Assessment.

Ethiopia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 10 cases reported in 2021.

Gambia
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week. There were 9 positive samples in 2021.

Ghana
• 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported in the Northern province this week making them the first in 2022 and since 2020.

Guinea
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 6 cases in 2021.

Guinea-Bissau
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases in the country which are linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria in 2021.

Israel
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 3 (cVDPV3) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in the country in 2022.

Liberia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases in 2021.

Madagascar
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There is 1 case in 2022. There were 13 cases in 2021..

Malawi
• No case of WPV1 was reported this week. In February [2022], the country reported the 1st WPV1 case on the continent since 2016, with onset of paralysis in November 2021.
• Following the first of a series of multi-country outbreak response implemented in March [2022], preparations are ongoing in both Malawi and neighbouring countries for the subsequent campaigns.
• In total, at least 4, multi-country campaigns will be implemented. Round 2 was successfully implemented last week across the country, with almost 3 million children reached, with independent monitoring indicating 94% coverage achieved.
• Lessons learned from the 1st round helped inform preparations for the 2nd campaign, including focusing on further strengthened coordination at all levels, microplanning, training and supervision, social mobilization and increased social mobilization and mass media engagement.
• At the same time, surveillance continues to be strengthened including at critical subnational levels.

Mauritania
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There were 7 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in 2021.

Mozambique
• Following confirmation of WPV1 last week, the Government of Malawi declared this outbreak to be a national public health emergency. The country is co-infected with WPV1 and cVDPV2.
• Genomic sequencing analysis indicates that the detected WPV1 is linked to a strain that had been circulating in Pakistan in 2019, similar to a WPV1 case reported in Malawi in February [2022].
• Detection of WPV1 in Mozambique confirms ongoing WPV1 transmissions in the sub-region. Mozambique has been actively participating in the multi-country emergency outbreak response implemented across the sub-region in response to the detected WPV1 in Malawi, alongside Tanzania, Zambia and Zimbabwe to reach more than 23 million children across the region during at least 4 multi-country emergency outbreak response campaigns. 2 rounds of bivalent OPV have already been implemented, the most recent at end-April [2022], with more than 4.2 million children vaccinated in Mozambique. At the same time, response in the country to the cVDPV2 outbreak is also ongoing.
• National and subnational authorities continue to be supported by partners of the Global Polio Eradication Initiative, notably by experts of the African Rapid Response Team and the GPLN.
• Detection of this most recent case underscores the appropriateness of the large-scale, rapid, multi-country emergency outbreak response across south-east Africa, in line with revised international polio outbreak response SOPs. The overriding priority is to continue to implement the subregional emergency response, by continuing to conduct large-scale, rapid and high-quality response campaigns.
• WHO considers there to be a continued high risk of international spread of this WPV1, particularly across the south-east subregion of Africa, due to persisting subnational immunity and surveillance gaps and large-scale population movements. The risk is magnified by decreased immunization rates related to the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic.

Niger
• 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported in Tillaberi making it the 2nd in 2022. There were 17 cases reported in 2021.
• 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported in Niamey.

Nigeria
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2022 cases remains 24. There were 415 cases reported in 2021.
• 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported in Kaduna.

Occupied Palestinian Territory
• No cVDPV3 positive environmental samples were reported this week.
• Bivalent OPV campaigns using fixed sites and mobile teams are being implemented in Bethlehem and Jerusalem, with R1 in mid-May [2022] and R2 a month later [June 2022].

Senegal
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 17 cases reported in 2021.

Sierra Leone
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 5 cases reported in 2021.

Somalia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2022. There was 1 case reported in 2021.
• 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported in Banadir.
• With the exception of Somaliland, the country concluded its mOPV2 NID in March 2022, covering 6 states. Somaliland has not yet confirmed its NID dates. Of the 2 669 790 under-5 children targeted in South, Central and Puntland, approximately 94% administrative coverage has been reported.

South Sudan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 9 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2021.

Uganda
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There were 2 positive samples linked to the N'Djamena outbreak in Chad reported in 2021.

Ukraine
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 2 cases reported in 2021.
• The national reference laboratory in Kiev has resumed routine testing of AFP cases, from 26 April 2022, and transportation of samples from provinces to Kiev as resumed.
• Routine immunization is continuing, though exact coverage and monitoring data are at this time difficult to verify.
• As part of the overall response to the crisis, UNICEF procured 5186 refrigerators and freezers, distribution is currently in process. As part of COVAX funding, 12 walk-in cold rooms with corresponding voltage stabilizers and real-time monitoring system were procured and are ready for shipment from Dubai. Eight 150 L freezers arrived in Lviv on 4 April 2022. Vaccine carriers and cold boxes (total of 5400) were delivered to Kiev and awaiting distribution to the service point level.

Yemen
• 12 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; Alhudaidah: 3; Almahaweet: 1; Dhamar: 2; Hajjah: 1; Ibb: 1; Lahaj: 1; Saadah: 1; Sanaa: 1; Sanaa City: 1. The number of cVDPV2 cases in 2022 now stands at 17. There were 61 cVDPV2 cases and 3 cVDPV1 cases in 2021.
• Intensive efforts are underway to access Yemen's northern governorates with polio vaccine, but until that happens, the outbreak's upward trajectory is expected to remain high.

Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of 24 May 2022
Wild poliovirus (WPV)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2022: 5 (compared with 2 for the same period in 2021)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2021: 6

Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) cases
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2022: 102 (compared with 91 for the same period in 2021)
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2021: 691

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[The above weekly report is very disconcerting. Overall there are 10 countries with evidence of circulation of polioviruses -- 2 countries with WPV1 and 8 with cVDPV2.\

There is the official confirmation of the 3rd WPV1 case in Pakistan (see Poliomyelitis update (18): WPV1 AFP Pakistan, cVDPV2 AFP, CVDPV3, violence 20220518.8703319 for the media report announcing the 3rd case), in addition to the positive environmental sample for WPV1 in Afghanistan -- confirming the continued circulation of the wild poliovirus in both Pakistan and Afghanistan.

Further disconcerting are the number of countries with ongoing cVDPV2 circulation reported in the past week -- 8 -- 4 with AFP cases (Chad, DR Congo, Niger, Yemen) and an additional 4 with no AFP cases but positive environmental samples (Djibouti, Ghana, Nigeria, Somalia). With this week's cases, both WPV1 and cVDPV cases reported to date in 2022 are more than those reported to date in 2021, suggesting increased pockets of susceptible individuals.

A map showing the locations of each confirmed case of polio worldwide in the past 12 months can be found at https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. One can see cases of cVDPV in a band across Africa and in Israel, Ukraine, Tajikistan, Afghanistan, and Pakistan; cVDPV1 in Madagascar and Yemen, and WPV1 in Afghanistan and Pakistan. - Mod.MPP]

******
[2] Pakistan WPV1 - 4th AFP case
Date: Thu 26 May 2022
Source: Dawn [edited]
https://www.dawn.com/news/1691536/pakistan-reports-fourth-polio-case-in-one-month


Pakistan reports 4th polio case in one month
--------------------------------------------
After having remained polio free for 15 months, the country on Wednesday [25 May 2022] reported the 4th polio case in one month.

The victim is a 13-month-old boy who has been paralysed by wild poliovirus in the Mir Ali area of North Waziristan tribal district in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa.

The case was confirmed by the Pakistan National Polio Laboratory at the National Institute of Health. This is the 3rd polio case from Mir Ali this year [2022].

"Another child in North Waziristan has been paralysed by wild poliovirus. This 13-month-old child will live with disabilities for the rest of his life because of a virus that is entirely preventable. This is a collective loss for Pakistan," said Health Minister Abdul Qadir Patel. "Over 99% of the world is now polio-free. Our children also deserve a life free from this incurable disease," he added.

"All parents must realise the risk that wild polio continues to pose to children all over Pakistan. Please ensure that your children are vaccinated in the ongoing nationwide campaign being conducted in all 156 districts of the country," he said.

According to preliminary investigations, the child had not received any dose of oral polio vaccine.

According to a statement, all children confirmed with wild polio this year [2022] belong to North Waziristan, where more cases are expected due to high refusal rates and instances of finger-marking without vaccination during the campaigns.

The nationwide immunisation campaign started on [23 May 2022] and will continue across the country till [27 May 2022].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[Please note that this case is the 4th case confirmed in Pakistan in 2022, whereas the case in the GPEI weekly update report is the 3rd case that was confirmed in Pakistan this year [2022]. And note that once again the child had no history of having been vaccinated.

A map of Pakistan showing districts and provinces can be seen at https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/pak215_pakistan_districts_v5_a0_20181203.pdf. - Mod.MPP

